message.content:
cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.TL, cs.DS, cs.FL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper introduces a calculus typable in a subsystem of linear logic.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper introduces a new lambda calculus and examines its expressivity with an algorithm.
- cs.TL (Theoretical Computer Science) is relevant as the paper deals with the complexity class PTIME and proves polynomial time reducibility.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper examines the expressivity of the calculus with an example algorithm.
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with a formal calculus and its expressivity.
